        <abstract>
            <p>Does not understand JDH on Pangenesis: on last page he appears to admit all that he regards as mere words on previous pages.</p>
            <p>Wallace admires chapter on Pangenesis.</p>
            <p>Pangenesis is a comfort. CD gains no idea from words like "potentiality" or "diffusing an influence"; atoms and cells give a distinct idea.</p> 
<p>A. Newton told George that Berthold Seemann wrote the <hi rend="italic">Athenæum</hi> review</p>  
<p>and that Lewis [Lewes] did not write the <hi rend="italic">Pall Mall Gazette</hi> review [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">5874</hi>].</p> 
        </abstract>
